  "Allegations" : "SEC Admin Release 34-80054/February 16, 2017: The Securities and Exchange Commission (Commission) deems it appropriate and in the public interest that public administrative proceedings be, and hereby are, instituted pursuant to Section 15(b) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (Exchange Act) against James P. Griffin. On July 22, 2015, the United States Attorney for the Northern District of New York (USAO) filed a criminal indictment against Griffin in United States v. Griffin, 15-cr-207 (N.D.N.Y.), alleging five counts of mail fraud, eight counts of wire fraud, and five counts of money laundering against Griffin. On July 30, 2015, the Commission filed a parallel civil action, SEC v. Griffin, 15-cv-0927 (N.D.N.Y.), naming Griffin and others as defendants. On November 25, 2015, the USAO filed a superseding indictment in United Sates v. Griffin. The Superseding Indictment charged Griffin with twenty-three separate criminal counts: 10 counts of mail fraud (pursuant to 18 U.S.C. \\u00a7 1341); 8 counts of wire fraud (pursuant to 18 U.S.C. \\u00a7 1343); and 5 counts of money laundering (pursuant to 18 U.S.C. \\u00a7\\u00a7 1957 and 2(b)). On February 2, 2016, the Court in SEC v. Griffin stayed that case, \"pending disposition of\" United States v. Griffin. On July 18, 2016, at the close of a seven-day trial, the jury in United States v. Griffin found Griffin guilty on all twenty-three counts of the Superseding Indictment. On July 25, 2016, the Court in SEC v. Griffin lifted its prior stay of that case, which remains pending before the United States District Court for the Northern District of New York. On December 16, 2016, the Court in United States v. Griffin entered its Judgment against Griffin, which sentences him, inter alia, to 60 months imprisonment (followed by three years of supervised release), and to pay restitution of $2,153,530.93.",
